This interceptor call `doAfterSuccessOrError(BiConsumer<? super T, Throwable> afterSuccessOrError)` method on return object. When an exception occurs during the stream  execution, the `accept(ClientResponse clientResponse, Throwable throwable)` method will be invoked with a throwable parameter and the first parameter will be null.

I think we can change `doAfterSuccessOrError(BiConsumer<? super T, Throwable> afterSuccessOrError) ` to `doOnSuccess(Consumer<? super T> onSuccess)`, the error will be handled on next `doOnError()` method.
